verbs.description: auscultate (third-person singular simple present auscultates, present participle auscultating, simple past and past participle auscultated)

entries.meaning: To listen (for example to the heart or lungs) by auscultation; to examine by auscultation.
examples: The doctor, listening past him, had had the same bovine stare as when he was auscultating.
